Rachel Eva Whitaker and Michael Joseph Wilper were married March 24 at the Greenpoint Loft, an events space in Brooklyn. Ronald J. Wilper, the father of the groom who was ordained through American Marriage Ministries, officiated.
Ms. Whitaker, 31, works in Manhattan as a television editor. Her credits include “The Late Show With Stephen Colbert” and the PBS series “The Mind of a Chef.” She graduated magna cum laude from Harvard.
She is the daughter of Alexis L. Gelber and Mark T. Whitaker of Manhattan. The bride’s father retired as the executive vice president and managing editor of CNN Worldwide based in Atlanta and is the author of “Smoketown,” a book on the history of the black community in Pittsburgh in the mid-20th century. Her mother is the editor in chief of Straus News-Manhattan, a group of weekly newspapers, and an adjunct professor at the Arthur L. Carter Journalism Institute at N.Y.U.
Mr. Wilper, 38, is a humanities teacher at the Berkeley Carroll School, a college prep school in Brooklyn. He graduated from the University of Idaho and received a master’s degree in philosophy from the University of Reading in Reading, England, and also received a master’s degree in education from Columbia.
He is a son of Ronald J. Wilper of Boise, Idaho, and the late Rita M. Wilper. The groom’s father is a retired district court judge in Idaho and a former president of the Idaho State Bar Association. The groom’s mother was a nurse at St. Luke’s Regional Medical Center in Boise.
The couple met in December 2014 on a blind date at Flatbush Farm, a restaurant in Brooklyn.
